.TH "rdma_rw_ctx_signature_init" 9 "rdma_rw_ctx_signature_init" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
rdma_rw_ctx_signature_init \- initialize a RW context with signature offload
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" rdma_rw_ctx_signature_init
.BI "(struct rdma_rw_ctx *ctx "  ","
.BI "struct ib_qp *qp "  ","
.BI "u8 port_num "  ","
.BI "struct scatterlist *sg "  ","
.BI "u32 sg_cnt "  ","
.BI "struct scatterlist *prot_sg "  ","
.BI "u32 prot_sg_cnt "  ","
.BI "struct ib_sig_attrs *sig_attrs "  ","
.BI "u64 remote_addr "  ","
.BI "u32 rkey "  ","
.BI "enum dma_data_direction dir "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ctx" 12
context to initialize
.IP "qp" 12
queue pair to operate on
.IP "port_num" 12
port num to which the connection is bound
.IP "sg" 12
scatterlist to READ/WRITE from/to
.IP "sg_cnt" 12
number of entries in \fIsg\fP
.IP "prot_sg" 12
scatterlist to READ/WRITE protection information from/to
.IP "prot_sg_cnt" 12
number of entries in \fIprot_sg\fP
.IP "sig_attrs" 12
signature offloading algorithms
.IP "remote_addr" 12
remote address to read/write (relative to \fIrkey\fP)
.IP "rkey" 12
remote key to operate on
.IP "dir" 12
DMA_TO_DEVICE for RDMA WRITE, DMA_FROM_DEVICE for RDMA READ
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Returns the number of WQEs that will be needed on the workqueue if
successful, or a negative error code.
